1.1
log
@md5(1) is now capable of doing md4, md5 and sha1 digests.  Currently
only md5 and sha1 are used.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
.\"	$OpenBSD$
d3 15
a17 8
.TH SHA1 1 "Jul 12, 1997"
.SH NAME
sha1 \- calculate a message-digest fingerprint (checksum) for a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sha1
[ -p | -t | -x | -sstring | filename(s) ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sha1
d23 3
a25 1
The SHA-1 algorithm is intended for digital signature applications, where a
d29 2
a30 2
.I RSA.
.SH OPTIONS
d33 1
a33 1
.B "filename(s)"
d35 8
a42 9
.in +5
.PP
.B -sstring
prints a checksum of the given "string".
.PP
.B -p
echos stdin to stdout and appends the SHA-1 sum to stdout.
.PP
.B -t
d44 1
a44 2
.PP
.B -x
d46 8
a53 7
.PP
.B filename(s)
prints a checksum(s) for each of the files.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR cksum (1)
.BR md5 (1)
.PP
d55 1
a55 1
.SH ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS
@
